    <element name="Flame Brilliance" type="Archetype Feature" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_ELEMENTALIST_FIRE_FLAME_BRILLIANCE">
        <description>
            <p>At 1st level, the creativity and cunning of fire afford you
new abilities. You gain proficiency with two skills of your
choice from Intimidation, Investigation, and Performance.
You also gain proficiency with light armor, shields, and simple
weapons. You can cast your elementalist spells even when
your hands are holding weapons or shields, performing the
necessary gestures to cast them.</p>
            <p class="indent">When wielding a weapon, your melee weapon attack
rolls can use your Wisdom modifier instead of Strength
or Dexterity. This modifier also applies to damage rolls
from the 6th level.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>You can cast your elementalist spells even when
your hands are holding weapons or shields, performing the
necessary gestures to cast them. When wielding a weapon, your melee weapon attack
rolls can use your Wisdom modifier instead of Strength
or Dexterity. This modifier also applies to damage rolls
from the 6th level.</description>
        </sheet>
        <rules>
            <select type="Proficiency" name="Skill Proficiency (Flame Brilliance)" number="2" supports="ID_PROFICIENCY_SKILL_INTIMIDATION|ID_PROFICIENCY_SKILL_INVESTIGATION|ID_PROFICIENCY_SKILL_PERFORMANCE" />
            <grant type="Proficiency" id="ID_PROFICIENCY_ARMOR_PROFICIENCY_LIGHT_ARMOR" />
            <grant type="Proficiency" id="ID_PROFICIENCY_ARMOR_PROFICIENCY_SHIELDS" />
            <grant type="Proficiency" id="ID_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY_SIMPLE_WEAPONS" />
        </rules>
    </element>
    <element name="Fiery Reprisal" type="Archetype Feature" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_ELEMENTALIST_FIRE_FIERY_REPRISAL">
        <description>
            <p>Starting at 6th level, when you are the target of an attack, you
can take a reaction to make a melee weapon attack against
an enemy within range.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet usage="Reaction">
            <description>when you are the target of an attack, you can take a reaction to make a melee weapon attack against an enemy within range.</description>
        </sheet>
    </element>
    <element name="Burning Inspiration" type="Archetype Feature" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_ELEMENTALIST_FIRE_BURNING_INSPIRATION">
        <description>
            <p>Starting at 10th level, you can use your connection with
Fire to inspire your allies. As a bonus action, you can imbue
yourself and all allies within 30 feet of you with the power
of flames, granting them an extra 1d6 fire damage to all
unarmed, weapon, or spell attacks. This effect lasts for 1
minute. After using this ability, you can’t use it again until
you complete a long rest.</p>
            <p class="indent"></p>
        </description>
        <sheet usage="1/long rest">
            <description>As a bonus action, you can imbue
yourself and all allies within 30 feet of you with the power
of flames, granting them an extra 1d6 fire damage to all
unarmed, weapon, or spell attacks. This effect lasts for 1
minute. After using this ability, you can’t use it again until
you complete a long rest.</description>
        </sheet>
    </element>
    <element name="Second Surge" type="Archetype Feature" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_ELEMENTALIST_FIRE_SECOND_SURGE">
        <description>
            <p>At 14th level, when using a spell slot to augment your elemental surge cantrip, you can use this cantrip again on the
next turn, as an action, as if you had spent a spell slot one
level lower.</p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
